{
  "text": "In SF2, we also observed that the NFBs and AMFs profiles depended on the season (Figure 4 ). Similar to the result of SF1, in the dry season, samples formed clusters for 16S-nifH gene based on soil depth ( Figure 4A ). Therefore, in same soil depth, there was no difference in microbial diversity among soybean field 1 (P13-16), native vegetation field (P17-20) and soybean field 2 (E21-24). This result may be due to the few microbial groups that can grow in low water availability. [CITATION_1] also obtained clusters of nifH and 18S rDNA genes by soil depth in the Cerrado.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "55203714"
